  <name>Bemudex</name>
  <summary>A modern desktop media downloader powered by yt-dlp and FFmpeg</summary>

  <icon type="stock">org.bemudex.Bemudex</icon>

  <description>
    <p>
      Bemudex is a modern desktop media downloader powered by yt-dlp and FFmpeg,
      built for Linux desktop environments with a modern, lightweight interface.
      Download videos, playlists, audio tracks and albums with metadata embedding,
      thumbnail support, queue management and automatic engine updates.
    </p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>High-quality video downloads</li>
      <li>MP3, FLAC, WAV and M4A audio downloads</li>
      <li>Playlist downloading support</li>
      <li>Metadata embedding</li>
      <li>Thumbnail embedding</li>
      <li>Chapter embedding</li>
      <li>Queue management</li>
      <li>Download retry support</li>
      <li>Custom thumbnail support</li>
      <li>Self-updating yt-dlp engine</li>
      <li>Automatic recovery from failed engine updates</li>
      <li>Modern desktop interface</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

  <launchable type="desktop-id">org.bemudex.Bemudex.desktop</launchable>

